passwords required for authentication software firmware and hardwareedit hypr software the hypr sdk software development kit can be embedded into applications to convert any mobile device into a biometric authenticator hypr enables developers and enterprises to deploy a secure passwordless experience across internal and consumer facing applications by enabling users to log in with tokenized biometrics through fingerprint sensors device cameras and microphones hypr adheres to the fido uaf authentication standards specified by the fast identity online alliance fido the hypr validation server can be implemented on premises or as a cloudbased deployment hypr firmware a firmware iteration of the hypr platform designed to secure use cases within the internet of things device manufacturers embed the hypr firmware to extend secure passwordless authentication to iot endpoints  with or without an internet connection in doing so devices such as locks for residential or commercial physical access as well as connected automobiles may leverage interoperable biometric tokenization protocols for user authentication hypr based authentication occurs over wifi over bluetooth low energy ble or near field communication nfc hypr hardware a fips  level  tamperproof security token that contains a fingerprint sensor and enables passwordless login for users in missioncritical settings where consumerfacing devices are prohibited the proprietary device communicates using bluetooth low energy ble and adheres to totp rfc standards and the fido uf authentication specifications designated by the fast identity online fido alliance historyedit hypr corp was founded in  in new york city by a team of security researchers with  in private seed capital before concluding a  million growth funding round in october  from new york based rtp ventures and boldstart ventures and taiwanbased mesh ventures hypr corp is a working group member of the fido fast identity online alliance a consortium of global enterprises working towards open standards for strong authentication the company’s biometric security technology was unveiled at the international consumer electronics show ces in january  in las vegas the hypr platform was featured as one of the top  best technologies of ces  by zdnet and has gone on to be implemented by enterprises across banking healthcare and ecommerce verticals hypr corp aims to differentiate its technology by providing enterprise customers an endtoend solution  complete with interoperable software firmware and hardware necessary to deploy biometric security at scale referencesedit  a b c d e blockchain meets biometrics as bitgo partners with hypr nasdaqcom retrieved    a b c d e f hypr biometric tokenization for payments  payment week payment week retrieved    a b c d bringing tokenization to secure payments  beyond dark reading retrieved     roy urrico august reprints  • hypr rethinks biometrics retrieved    reality check in search of better authentication in an iot world rcr wireless news retrieved    tanaya macheel biometric startup raises growth capital american banker retrieved  october    zakrzewski cat  october  wsj pro venture capital retrieved  october  – via wall street journal   a b c d e biometric encryption  hypr cryptography hypr biometric security  retrieved    a b c hypr debuts biometrics sdk to improve authentication wwweweekcom retrieved    seals tara hypr rolls out biometrics sdk for mobile apps iot infosecurity magazine retrieved    mobile wallets are not securing data as it goes to the cloud paymentssource retrieved    biometric security authentication for a more secure iot  itproportalcom retrieved    ces  meet this years best tech   page   zdnet zdnet retrieved    the hypr lets you make secure payments with your finger cnet retrieved    kolodny lora hypr raises  million to keep hackers from getting their hands on your fingerprints techcrunch retrieved    ces  meet this years best tech   page   zdnet zdnet retrieved   external 