g sensitive biometric authentication data to the internet user credentials are stored locally and tokenized  preventing malicious rd parties from reusing compromised credentials by combining the user experience of biometric tokenization with the strength of public key cryptography hypr provides a decentralized biometric authentication scheme to replace the use of centralized passwordbased systems the result of implementing biometric tokenization is an “inverted” authentication channel in which hackers are unable to gain credentials by attacking a centralized repository of biometrics and are forced to target individual user devices by forcing malicious attackers to divert attention from a centralized validation server to many clientside devices biometric tokenization decreases the viability of an attack on the clientserver authentication channel rendering the common largescale serverside data breach an unscalable attack vector according to hypr corp hypr technology is designed based on the following principles authentication channels should not be based on centralized biometrics storage users may have the option to choose the biometric authenticators they would like to utilize isolation of biometric data from the rich operating system on a user device relying parties may have the capability to set policies to use biometric authenticators hypr platformedit the hypr platform provides enterprises an endtoend suite of software firmware and hardware to enable decentralized biometric security for data across mobile desktop and iot systems as an interoperable solution users may choose from a variety of biometric authentication methods by leveraging existing fingerprint sensors cameras and microphones on mobile devices hypr is available as a cross platform sdk for byod deployment or as a tamper proof security token for mission critical settings the hypr biometric security platform seeks to secure the use of biometrics and to enhance user experience through passwordless authentication users of applications with embedded hypr technology do not need to create remember securely store or reset passwords because there aren’t any passwords required for authentication software firmware and hardwareedit hypr software the hypr sdk software development kit can be embedded into applications to convert any mobile device into a biometric authenticator hypr enables developers and enterprises to deploy a secure passwordless experience across internal and consumer facing applications by enabling users to log in with tokenized biometrics through fingerprint sensors device cameras and microphones hypr adheres to the fido uaf authentication standards specified by the fast identity online alliance fido the hypr validation server can be implemented on premises or as a cloudbased deployment hypr firmware a firmware iteration of the hypr platform designed to secure use cases within the internet of things device manufacturers embed the hypr firmware to extend secure passwordless authentication to iot endpoints  with or without an internet connection in doing so devices such as locks for residential or commercial physical access as well as connected automobiles may leverage interoperable biometric tokenization protocols for user authentication hypr based authentication occurs over wifi over bluetooth low energy ble or near field communication nfc hypr hardware a fips  level  tamperproof security token that contains a fingerprint sensor and enables passwordless login for users in missioncritical settings where consumerfacing devices are prohibited the proprietary device communicates using bluetooth low energy ble and adheres to totp rfc standards and the fido uf authentication specifications designated by the fast identity online fido alliance historyedit hypr corp was founded in  in new york city by a team of security researchers with  in private seed capital before concluding a  million growth funding round in october  from new york based rtp ventures and boldstart ventures and taiwanbased mesh ventures hypr corp is a working group member of the fido fast identity online alliance a consortium of global enterprises working towards open standards for strong authentication the company’s biometric security technology was unveiled at the international consumer electronics show ces in january  in las vegas the hypr platform was featured as one of the top  best technologies of ces  by zdnet and has gone on to be implemented by enterprises across banking healthcare and ecommerce verticals hypr corp aims to differentiate its technology by providing enterprise customers an endtoend solution  complete with interoperable software firmware and hardware necessary to deploy biometric security at scale referencesedit  a b c d e blockchain meets biometrics as bitgo partners with hypr nasdaqcom retrieved    a b c d e f hypr biometric tokenization for payments  payment week payment week retrieved    a b c d bringing tokenization to secure payments  beyond dark reading retrieved     roy urrico august reprints  • hypr rethinks biometrics retrieved    reality check in search of better authentication in an iot world rcr wireless news retrieved    tanaya macheel biometric startup raises growth capital american banker retrieved  october    zakrzewski cat  october  wsj pro venture capital retrieved  october  – via wall street journal   a b c d e biometric encryption  hypr cryptography hypr biometric security  retrieved    a b c hypr debuts biometrics sdk to improve authentication wwweweekcom retrieved    seals tara hypr rolls out biometrics sdk for mobile apps iot infosecurity magazine retrieved    mobile wallets are not securing data as it goes to the cloud paymentssource retrieved    biometric security authentication for a more secure iot  itproportalcom retrieved    ces  meet this years best tech   page   zdnet zdnet retrieved    the hypr lets you make secure payments with your finger cnet retrieved    kolodny lora hypr raises  million to keep